ecessary to replace the template used within the portal to ensure medical comments are li</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nked to the mechanical evidence and observation on functionality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">       </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Further information in support of a claim</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Whilst we understand that further information to support a claim would be welcome, we would caution against a requirement to see a medical practitioner shortly after an accident. The system </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">could </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">be worked in such a way to ensure compliance with any proces</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s with the result that this would inevitably impact on limited NHS resources.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-